{
  "id": "ary-a1-u1",
  "title": "Salam",
  "level": "A1",
  "summary": "Greetings, politeness, and how to give your name.",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "id": "l1",
      "title": "Hello and thanks",
      "teach": [
        {
          "target": "Salam",
          "roman": "salam",
          "arabic": "سَلَام",
          "english": "hello / peace",
          "note": "Short for 'salamu alaykum' — works for anyone, any time of day.",
          "ipa": "salˌaːm",
          "audio": "audio/salam.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Sbah lkhir",
          "roman": "sbah lkhir",
          "arabic": "صْبَاح لْخِير",
          "english": "good morning",
          "ipa": "s̪bˈaːħ lχˈiːr",
          "audio": "audio/sbah-lkhir.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Msa lkhir",
          "roman": "msa lkhir",
          "arabic": "مْسَا لْخِير",
          "english": "good evening",
          "ipa": "msˈaː lχˈiːr",
          "audio": "audio/msa-lkhir.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Shukran",
          "roman": "shukran",
          "arabic": "شُكْرًا",
          "english": "thank you",
          "ipa": "ʃˈukran",
          "audio": "audio/shukran.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "3afak",
          "roman": "3afak",
          "arabic": "عَفَاكْ",
          "english": "please",
          "note": "The 3 stands for ع (ayn), a throat sound Latin script has no letter for — this Arabizi digit convention (2, 3, 7, 9...) is what Moroccans actually type.",
          "ipa": "ʕˈafaːk",
          "audio": "audio/3afak.wav"
        }
      ],
      "grammar": {
        "title": "Darija has no 'to be' in the present",
        "body": "Like other Arabic varieties, Darija just drops the present-tense verb 'to be' — *huwa m3llem* means 'he [is a] teacher', no verb needed. You'll see this constantly: describing, naming, and pointing things out never needs an extra word for 'is/am/are'."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l2",
      "title": "Yes, no, goodbye",
      "teach": [
        {
          "target": "Ih",
          "roman": "ih",
          "arabic": "إِيه",
          "english": "yes",
          "note": "The everyday, casual yes — na3am exists too but sounds more formal.",
          "ipa": "ʔˈiːh",
          "audio": "audio/ih.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "La",
          "roman": "la",
          "arabic": "لَا",
          "english": "no",
          "ipa": "laː",
          "audio": "audio/la.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Bslama",
          "roman": "bslama",
          "arabic": "بْسْلَامَا",
          "english": "goodbye",
          "ipa": "bslˈaːmaː",
          "audio": "audio/bslama.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Smehli",
          "roman": "smehli",
          "arabic": "سْمَحْلِي",
          "english": "sorry / excuse me",
          "ipa": "smˈaħliː",
          "audio": "audio/smehli.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Labas?",
          "roman": "labas",
          "arabic": "لَابَاسْ",
          "english": "how are you? (lit. 'no harm?')",
          "note": "The standard how-are-you. Answer is usually the same word back: Labas, lhamdullah — 'fine, thank God'.",
          "ipa": "laːbˌaːs",
          "audio": "audio/labas.wav"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "l3",
      "title": "Smiti — my name",
      "teach": [
        {
          "target": "Smiti...",
          "roman": "smiti",
          "arabic": "سْمِيتِي",
          "english": "my name is...",
          "ipa": "smˈiːtiː",
          "audio": "audio/smiti.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Ash smitek?",
          "roman": "ash smitek",
          "arabic": "آش سْمِيتَك",
          "english": "what's your name?",
          "ipa": "ʔˈaːʃ smˈiːtakˌa",
          "audio": "audio/ash-smitek.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Mtsharfin",
          "roman": "mtsharfin",
          "arabic": "مْتْشَرْفِين",
          "english": "nice to meet you",
          "ipa": "mtʃˈarfiːn",
          "audio": "audio/mtsharfin.wav"
        },
        {
          "target": "Wakha",
          "roman": "wakha",
          "arabic": "وَاخَا",
          "english": "okay",
          "ipa": "wˈaːχaː",
          "audio": "audio/wakha.wav"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "canDo": [
    "Greet someone and say goodbye",
    "Ask and answer \"how are you?\"",
    "Give your name and ask someone else's"
  ]
}
